This paper deals with power control in wireless ad hoc networks, which is a topic related to networking and communication (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the optimization of power control, which involves mathematical modeling and analysis (cs.IT). The proposed scheme involves clustering of nodes, which is a common technique in machine learning and data analysis (cs.MA). The paper also discusses the performance metrics of transmission capacity and outage probability, which are related to system dynamics and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper involves simulation experiments, which are related to multimedia (cs.MM).
